// tsconfig.json — TypeScript Compiler Options
// ============================================
//
// Controls how TypeScript type-checks the source files.
// Vite handles the actual compilation (transpilation) — TypeScript here
// is used ONLY for type checking (noEmit: true).
//
// KEY OPTIONS EXPLAINED:
//
//   "target": "ES2020"
//     Defines what JavaScript features TypeScript assumes are available.
//     ES2020 supports async/await, optional chaining, nullish coalescing natively.
//
//   "module": "ESNext"
//     Use ES module syntax (import/export). Required by Vite's module system.
//
//   "jsx": "react-jsx"
//     Use the new React 17+ JSX transform. You do NOT need to import React
//     in every file — the transform handles it automatically.
//
//   "strict": true
//     Enables all strict type-checking flags. Catches more bugs at compile time.
//     Includes: strictNullChecks, noImplicitAny, strictFunctionTypes, etc.
//
//   "moduleResolution": "bundler"
//     Vite-compatible module resolution strategy. Resolves bare imports
//     the same way Vite does at build time.
//
//   "noEmit": true
//     TypeScript only type-checks, never writes output files.
//     Vite handles compilation via its own pipeline (esbuild).
//
//   "include": ["src"]
//     Only type-check files inside src/. Config files and node_modules are excluded.